'''Ahmed Fathy Mansi Abdulla''' (also spelled '''Fatehi''', {{langx|ar|أحمد فتحي}}, born 25 January 1993) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/ahmed-fatehi/267542/ |title=Ahmed Fathy |website=Soccerway |access-date=22 April 2020|publisher=Perform Group}}</ref> Born in [[Egypt]], he represents the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Career==
Fathy began his professional career with [[Al-Arabi SC (Qatar)|Al-Arabi]] in 2012. After several years living in Qatar, he was granted Qatari citizenship and represented the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]]. He was a member of the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]] and [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] winning team.{{citation needed|date=October 2025}}

